 is totally unacceptable. I don't remember how I ended up lying on the road. I don't remember a whole lot.</p><p>\"From what I remember, the officers didn't say anything to me before they left. I was drunk, yes, but they could at least have left me on the footpath. It's out of order, it's as simple as that.</p><p>\"It's not their job to do that. I cried when I saw the footage. I am a human being, you know.\"</p><p>The 23-year-old added: \"They should lose their jobs now. If they did to me, they could do it to everyone. I am an alcoholic and I'm not proud of it, but they what they did on Monday was unacceptable.\"</p><p>The police ombudsman in Northern Ireland has opened an investigation into the incident, which was filmed by a member of the public and widely distributed on the BBC, Facebook and other social networks.</p><p>The incident happened in John Street during the annual St Patrick's Day celebrations.</p>","headline":"Derry woman calls for sacking of police officers who left in her in a bus lane","trailText":"Police ombudsman opens investigation into St Patrick's Day incident seen on BBC and social networks","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/20/1395323091817/Derry-Bridget-Mongan-004.jpg","wordcount":"235","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-03-23T13:54:57Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/mar/20/derry-woman-left-bus-lane","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk-news/2014/mar/20/derry-woman-left-bus-lane","tags":[{"id":"uk/uk","webTitle":"UK news","type":"keyword","sectionId":"uk-news","sectionName":"UK news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk/uk","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk/uk","references":[]},{"id":"uk/derry","webTitle":"Derry","type":"keyword","sectionId":"uk-news","sectionName":"UK news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk/derry","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk/derry","references":[]},{"id":"uk/police","webTitle":"Police"